</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5FB46516FF91FFC8D387FCE8FB4DFC56" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1711369DFF91FFC8D387FCE8FB4DFC56" blockId="16.[151,1436,258,967]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D387FCE8FEC5FCCB" bold="true" box="[199,315,834,859]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF91FFC8D203FCEEFE25FCCB" box="[323,475,834,859]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zeylanicus">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D203FCEEFE25FCCB" box="[323,475,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">H. zeylanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF91FFC8D11DFCEEFD30FCCB" box="[605,718,836,859]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pronus">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D11DFCEEFD30FCCB" box="[605,718,836,859]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">H. pronus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the male genitalia characters, but differs in the shape of the aedeagal shafts and the basal processes. In 
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF91FFC8D13CFCCDFCECFCEF" box="[636,786,870,895]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zeylanicus">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D13CFCCDFCECFCEF" box="[636,786,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">H. zeylanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the shafts are very broad at the base and inwardly curved at distal 
<number id="A16624BAFF91FFC8D3B4FC21FEDBFC33" box="[244,293,907,931]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" value="0.33">0.33</number>
length whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF91FFC8D2B7FC26FD98FC33" box="[503,614,908,931]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pronus">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D2B7FC26FD98FC33" box="[503,614,908,931]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">H. pronus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the shafts are uniform in width and not so curved in posterior view, but in lateral view the shafts in 
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF91FFC8D2EFFC05FDE1FC56" box="[431,543,943,966]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pronus">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D2EFFC05FDE1FC56" box="[431,543,943,966]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">H. pronus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are strongly sinuate which is not the case in 
<taxonomicName id="D0AE4D1EFF91FFC8D755FC05FB55FC57" box="[1045,1195,942,967]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zeylanicus">
<emphasis id="25DAEA8FFF91FFC8D755FC05FB55FC57" box="[1045,1195,942,967]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="117">H. zeylanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
